<% content_for :title do %>
  Clio
<% end %>
<div style="height: 100px;"></div>
<div class="mx-5 text-light">
  <div class="row justify-content-center align-items-center mx-0 mb-5">
    <div class="col-auto text-center">
      <%= image_tag("clio logo.png", alt: "Clio", height: 80) %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-auto ps-4">
      <p class="fw-bold font-monospace my-0" style="font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 3rem);">Software Developer</p>
      <p class="text-opacity-75 font-monospace my-0" style="font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem);">January 2025 &ndash; August 2025 &middot; Vancouver, BC</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div style="height: 40px;"></div>
  <div class="row mx-0 justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-lg-9 col-xxl-8">
      <p class="text-start text-opacity-75 mb-4" style="font-size: 1.15rem;">
        At Clio, I worked as a Software Developer on the Identity team, engineering OAuth 2.0 authentication
        flows using Ruby on Rails and ORY Hydra. This centralized identity services across six customer-facing
        applications — Manage, Grow, Accounting, Draft, Identity, and Admin — and laid the foundation for a
        company-wide rollout of mandated multi-factor authentication.
      </p>
      <p class="text-start text-opacity-75 mb-4" style="font-size: 1.15rem;">
        A major focus of my work was migrating 100% of legacy authentication systems to the unified Identity
        platform, reducing authentication errors and simplifying future MFA rollouts. I designed and implemented
        Warden-based SAML and SSO integrations that enabled independent law firms to configure secure,
        multi-tenant access into Clio's application suite — giving firms direct control over their own identity
        providers.
      </p>
      <p class="text-start text-opacity-75 mb-4" style="font-size: 1.15rem;">
        Throughout my term I collaborated closely with product, security, and DevOps teams to architect scalable
        backend services and automate CI/CD pipelines, ensuring authentication changes were thoroughly validated
        across development, testing, and staging environments before reaching customers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div style="height: 150px;"></div>